<section class="white-bg">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-7">
                <h2 class="pageHeading">Partnership to LLP</h2>
                <p class="text-justify">After implementation of Limited Liability Partnership (LLP), more and more Partnership Firms are converting themselves to Limited Liability Partnership (LLP) for obvious reasons of unlimited number of Partners, perpetual succession, limited liability, transferability, tax benefits, less accountability, flexibity etc.</p>
                <h2 class="pageHeading">Advantages of Limited Liability Partnership</h2>
                <div class="essential">
                    <h4>Carry Forward and Set off Losses and Unabsorbed Depreciation </h4>
                    <p class="text-justify">The accumulated loss and unabsorbed depreciation of firm is deemed to be loss/ depreciation of the successor LLP for the previous year in which conversion was effected. Thus such loss can be carried for further eight years in the hands of the successor LLP.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="essential">
                    <h4>No Stamp Duty </h4>
                    <p class="text-justify">LLP automatically vest all movable and immovable properties of the firm. No instrument of transfer is required to be executed and hence no stamp duty is required to be paid.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="essential">
                    <h4>Continuation of Brand Value </h4>
                    <p class="text-justify"><p>It continues to enjoy the previous success story with legal recognition and the goodwill of the firm and its brand value is kept intact.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="essential">
                    <h4>Automatic transfer</h4>
                    <p class="text-justify">Before the conversion, all the assets and liabilities of the firm immediately become the assets and liabilities of the LLP.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="essential">
                    <h4>No Capital Gain Tax </h4>
                    <p class="text-justify">On transfer of property from firm to LLP no Capital Gains tax shall be charged.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

